         <abstract>
            <p>In 1940, a Mahler proposed a conjecture regarding the value of best $P$-adic Diophantine approximation constants. In this paper, a computational technique which tests the conjecture for any particular $P$ is described. A computer search verified the conjecture for all $P \leqslant 101$, except 83. The case $P = 83$ is discussed. A counterexample is given.</p>
          </abstract>
